The paper deals with the downlink of a massive multiuser MIMO system, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of orthogonal frequency division multiplexing (OFDM) and the consideration of oversampling DACs suggest a focus on signal processing (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also discusses the practical implications of low-resolution DACs, which could fall under computer communications (cs.COM).
